<h3>Payments and Revenue Management</h3>

Glofox integrates with Stripe and GoCardless, giving operators competitive processing rates (typically 2.4-2.9% + $0.30 per transaction). Revenue reporting is straightforward with clear MRR tracking and churn metrics.

Mindbody's built-in payment processing runs higher (2.75%+ in most configurations) but offers tighter integration with their POS system. For gyms selling significant retail or supplements, Mindbody's unified commerce approach reduces reconciliation headaches.

<h3>Marketing and Lead Generation</h3>

Mindbody's consumer marketplace is genuinely valuable for discovery. Our data shows new Mindbody operators in competitive markets can expect 15-30 marketplace-sourced leads monthly in year one. That number drops significantly after initial launch but remains a steady trickle.

Glofox relies on operators driving their own traffic but provides better conversion tools. Landing pages, lead capture forms, and trial-to-member automation outperform Mindbody's equivalent features in our A/B testing across multiple gym launches.

<h3>Reporting and Analytics</h3>

Glofox's reporting has improved dramatically since 2024. The new dashboard provides real-time attendance tracking, revenue forecasting, and member health scores. Data exports cleanly to spreadsheets.

Mindbody offers deeper analytics but locks the best reports behind higher tiers. The standard reports are adequate; the premium reports are genuinely useful for operators obsessed with metrics. Expect to pay an additional $100-200/month for access.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Tip:</strong> Regardless of platform, export your data monthly to a separate system. Both Glofox and Mindbody make migration painful if you don't maintain clean member records independently. We recommend a simple Airtable backup of member contact info, membership types, and billing dates.
</div>

