<h2 id="who-its-for">🎯 Who Each Platform Is For</h2>

<strong>Choose Glofox if:</strong>
<ul>
  <li>You run a boutique fitness studio (CrossFit, yoga, pilates, martial arts, functional training)</li>
  <li>Mobile app experience is a priority for member retention</li>
  <li>You're scaling from 1 to 15 locations and need clean multi-site management</li>
  <li>Budget matters and you want premium features without enterprise pricing</li>
  <li>Your business is pure fitness without significant spa or retail components</li>
</ul>

<strong>Choose Mindbody if:</strong>
<ul>
  <li>You operate a hybrid wellness facility (gym + spa + salon + retail)</li>
  <li>Organic lead generation from the Mindbody marketplace matters to your acquisition strategy</li>
  <li>You're running 20+ locations and need enterprise-grade reporting for investors or franchisors</li>
  <li>Your staff already knows Mindbody and switching costs outweigh savings</li>
  <li>You need deep integrations with industry-specific tools (spa software, salon booking, etc.)</li>
</ul>

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Tip:</strong> If you're currently on Mindbody and considering a switch, run the numbers on your actual marketplace-sourced member revenue. Many operators overestimate marketplace value—pull reports on members acquired through Mindbody discovery versus your own marketing channels. If marketplace contributes less than 10% of new members, the premium likely isn't justified.
</div>

<h2 id="migration-considerations">🔄 Migration Considerations</h2>

Switching platforms mid-operation is painful. Our team has managed dozens of gym software migrations, and the real costs are rarely in the software itself.

<strong>Data migration:</strong> Both platforms export member data reasonably well. The challenge is historical attendance records, billing history, and contract terms. Budget 20-40 hours of staff time for a 500-member gym migration, regardless of direction.

<strong>Member communication:</strong> App transitions confuse members. Expect a 5-10% uptick in support requests during the first month post-switch. Pre-record video walkthroughs of the new booking flow to minimize friction.

<strong>Payment re-authorization:</strong> Moving between payment processors requires members to re-authorize cards. Industry standard is 85-92% successful re-authorization on first attempt. Budget for manual follow-up on the remainder.

<strong>Contract timing:</strong> Both platforms enforce annual contracts at mid-tiers and above. Time your evaluation to coincide with renewal windows. Starting a new annual agreement just before you want to switch is expensive.

For a deeper dive on planning technology transitions, see our guide on [gym software migration best practices](/guides/gym-software-migration).

<h2 id="integration-ecosystems">🔌 Integration Ecosystems</h2>

Mindbody's integration advantage is real but narrowing. The platform connects with over 100 third-party tools spanning marketing automation, HR systems, accounting software, and fitness-specific apps like heart rate monitors and body composition scanners.

Glofox has prioritized quality over quantity, focusing on integrations that fitness operators actually use: Stripe, Mailchimp, Zapier, and key hardware partners. The Zapier connection opens thousands of indirect integrations, though with more configuration required.

